This week, I solved several medium-level challenges in picoCTF including St3go, Sleuthkit Intro, Sleuthkit Apprentice, Redaction Gone Wrong, Packets Primer, Operation Orchid, Operation Oni, Lookey Here, File Types, Enhance!, Eavesdrop, WPA-ing Out, Advanced Potion Making, and Milkslap. These challenges focused on digital forensics, steganography, file analysis, and network traffic investigation.

During these tasks, I learned how to analyze disk images using tools from The Sleuth Kit and inspect network packet captures using Wireshark. I also practiced identifying hidden data in files by checking file signatures, analyzing metadata, and decoding encoded information.

One challenge this week was deciding which tools or techniques to use first when analyzing a file or packet capture. However, by carefully reading hints and testing different approaches, I was able to solve the problems.

Overall, this week improved my skills in digital forensics, file investigation, and network analysis, and helped me become more comfortable using cybersecurity tools and command-line techniques.
